    "24 However, generalized access to content data would be irreconcilable with the essence of the right to privacy; see CJEU, Maximillian Schrems v Data Protection Commissioner, judgment of 6 October 2015, Case C-362/14, §94.",
    "Given the sensitivity of the inferences possible from IXR metadata, their retention would not comply with the proportionality principle. 25",
    "Repealing Directive 2002/58/EC (Regulation on Privacy and Electronic Communications), 10.1.2017. such, 26 prompting Meta to shift to the \"legitimate interests\" clause.",
    "However, TikTok was warned that its \"legitimate interests\" were not sufficient to justify processing for targeted advertising (Lomas, 2023).",
    "If it does end up being used, however, the \"legitimate interests\" basis requires users to be able to opt out of the processing (Bryant, 2023), providing additional protection to users should it be implemented effectively."
